<h1>ğŸ½ï¸ Mom's Kitchen</h1>

<p >
  <b>Mom's Kitchen</b> is an Android-based food ordering application built as if a restaurant created its own delivery system.
  The app focuses on simplicity, smooth navigation, and real-world ordering flow.
</p>

<hr/>

<h2>ğŸ“± About the App</h2>

<p>
Mom's Kitchen allows users to browse food items, manage favorites and cart, place orders, and track their order history.
The app is designed to simulate a real restaurant workflow rather than a large aggregator like Swiggy or Zomato.
</p>

<p>
From authentication to order confirmation, every step is handled inside the app to provide a complete end-to-end ordering experience.
</p>

<hr/>

<h2>ğŸ”„ App Flow</h2>

<ul>
  <li>User signs up or logs in using email authentication</li>
  <li>Email verification ensures only valid users can access the app</li>
  <li>Menu items are displayed category-wise from the database</li>
  <li>Users can add items to favorites or cart</li>
  <li>Cart allows quantity selection and order confirmation</li>
  <li>Address details are filled using location services</li>
  <li>After placing an order, users can view it in order history</li>
  <li>Profile section displays user information and logout option</li>
</ul>

<hr/>

<h2>âœ¨ Key Features</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Category-based menu browsing ğŸ•ğŸ¥—</li>
  <li>Favorites and cart management â¤ï¸ğŸ›’</li>
